On International Women's Day, the US government celebrates the contributions of women and reaffirms its commitment to ensuring equal opportunities for everyone. Despite progress, many women still face barriers in various aspects of life. The Trump administration has implemented initiatives to promote women's economic empowerment, such as the Women Entrepreneurs Finance Initiative and the Canada-United States Council for Advancement of Women Entrepreneurs and Business Leaders. They are also mobilizing $1 billion for projects that support women in emerging markets. The Women, Peace, and Security Act promote the participation of women in conflict prevention and peace efforts globally. The administration is launching the WomenConnect Challenge to provide women in developing countries with access to digital technology. In the US, the Small Business Administration has increased capital loans to women-owned businesses. These initiatives aim to empower women to achieve their economic potential and enhance women's leadership globally.